-- Mexico Landslide in Oaxaca State Leaves Hundreds Dead, Excelsior Reports
-- B y   J o s e   E n r i q u e   A r r i o j a
-- 2010-09-28T12:48:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/mexico-landslide-in-oaxaca-state-leaves-hundreds-dead-excelsior-reports.html
A landslide in the Mexican state of
Oaxaca left hundreds dead and 300 families homeless, Excelsior
reported citing state civil protection authorities.  Severe rains caused a landside in the town of Santa Maria
Tlahuitoltepec, Oaxaca, Mexico City-based Excelsior reported
citing Carlos Ramos Aragon, director of the state civil
protection service.  The landslide started around 4:00 am local time,according
to the newspaper. Soldiers and rescue workers are being
mobilized to the town, Excelsior reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jose Enrique Arrioja at 
 jarrioja@bloomberg.net  